creator: Arthur Hugh Clough
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 14 recordings of Say Not the Struggle Naught Availeth by Arthur Hugh Clough. This was the Weekly Poetry project for November 8, 2105 Read in English by ABabington; Bruce Kachuk; bsdarby; Christie Crews; David Lawrence; Newgatenovelist; Greg Giordano; Ian King; Joe Brenneman; John Burlinson; J. McDougall; Lee Ann Howlett; MaryAnn and Maria Kasper. Arthur Hugh Clough (kluf) was an English poet, an educationalist, and the devoted assistant to ground-breaking nurse Florence Nightingale. He was the brother of suffragist Anne Clough, who became principal of Newnham College, Cambridge. ( Wikipedia) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
